# Privacy Policy for Grims Guide Discord Bot

**Last Updated:** 02/06/2026

**Bot Owner:** Kristopher W. Lee  
**Contact:** The Grim Viking or thereapersarmygaming@gmail.com

---

## 1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy explains how Grims Guide ("the Bot," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, stores, and protects your information when you use our Discord bot.

By using the Bot, you consent to the data practices described in this policy. If you do not agree with this policy, please do not use the Bot.

## 2. Information We Collect

### 2.1 Automatically Collected Data

When you use the Bot, we automatically collect:

**Server Information:**
- Server ID (unique identifier for your Discord server)
- Server name (for logging and support purposes)
- Channel IDs (where Bot commands are used)

**User Information:**
- User ID (unique Discord identifier)
- Username (for display in commands and logs)
- User roles and permissions (to verify command access)

**Command Usage Data:**
- Commands executed
- Timestamp of command usage
- Command parameters (e.g., poll questions, giveaway prizes)

### 2.2 User-Provided Data

Information you explicitly provide through Bot commands:

**Configuration Data:**
- Donation links (PayPal, Ko-fi, etc.)
- Custom donation messages
- Welcome messages
- Auto-role settings
- Translation preferences
- Channel configurations

**Content Data:**
- Poll questions and options
- Giveaway descriptions and prizes
- Auction listings (for WoW features)
- Moderation notes and warnings
- Suggestion submissions

**Message Data (Limited):**
- Message IDs (for polls, giveaways, and specific features)
- Message content (only for translation feature, not permanently stored)

### 2.3 Data We Do NOT Collect

We do not collect:
- Message content (except temporarily for translation)
- Private/Direct Messages
- Voice data
- Payment information
- Personal identifiable information (email, phone, address)
- IP addresses
- Device information

## 3. How We Use Your Information

### 3.1 Service Provision

We use collected data to:
- Provide Bot functionality (moderation, polls, giveaways, etc.)
- Store server configuration and preferences
- Track giveaway entries and poll votes
- Maintain moderation logs and warnings
- Execute translation services

### 3.2 Service Improvement

We may use data to:
- Analyze feature usage and popularity
- Identify and fix bugs
- Improve Bot performance
- Develop new features

### 3.3 Support and Communication

We use data to:
- Respond to support requests
- Investigate reported issues
- Communicate Bot updates

### 3.4 Legal Compliance

We may use or disclose data to:
- Comply with legal obligations
- Protect against illegal activities
- Enforce our Terms of Service
- Protect the rights and safety of users

## 4. Data Storage and Security

### 4.1 Storage Location

Data is stored in:
- Local JSON files on the Bot's server
- Location: United States Of America

### 4.2 Security Measures

We implement reasonable security measures:
- Restricted file access (Bot owner only)
- Regular data backups
- Encrypted API communications (HTTPS)
- Secure storage practices

### 4.3 Data Retention

**Active Data:**
- Configuration data: Retained while Bot is in your server
- Moderation logs: Retained indefinitely or until deleted by admin
- Giveaway/Poll data: Retained until completion + 30 days
- Warning data: Retained until manually cleared

**Inactive Data:**
- If Bot is removed from your server, data is retained for 30 days
- After 30 days, server data may be automatically purged
- You may request immediate deletion (see Section 8)

## 5. Data Sharing

### 5.1 Third-Party Services

The Bot uses these third-party services which may process your data:

**Discord API:**
- Purpose: Bot functionality
- Data shared: User IDs, Server IDs, Messages (as needed)
- Privacy Policy: https://discord.com/privacy

**Google Gemini AI:**
- Purpose: Message translation
- Data shared: Message text (temporarily, not stored by Google)
- Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

### 5.2 No Selling of Data

We do NOT:
- Sell your data to third parties
- Share your data for marketing purposes
- Provide your data to advertisers

### 5.3 Legal Disclosure

We may disclose data if required by:
- Court orders or subpoenas
- Law enforcement requests
- Legal compliance requirements

## 6. User Rights

### 6.1 Access Rights

You have the right to:
- Request a copy of your data
- Know what data we store about you
- Understand how your data is used

### 6.2 Correction Rights

You can:
- Update your server's configuration data
- Modify poll/giveaway content before completion
- Correct inaccurate information

### 6.3 Deletion Rights

You can request:
- Deletion of specific data entries
- Complete server data removal
- Removal from Bot's database

**How to Exercise Rights:**
Contact the Bot owner at Discord or Email.

## 7. Children's Privacy

### 7.1 Age Requirements

The Bot is not intended for users under 13 years old (or minimum age required by Discord).

### 7.2 Parental Consent

If you are under 18, ensure you have parental permission before using the Bot.

### 7.3 Data from Minors

We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13. If we discover such data, we will delete it immediately.

## 8. Data Deletion Requests

### 8.1 How to Request Deletion

To delete your data:
1. Contact the Bot owner via Discord or Email
2. Provide your Server ID or User ID
3. Specify what data you want deleted

### 8.2 Deletion Timeline

- Request acknowledged within: 48 hours
- Data deleted within: 7 business days
- Confirmation sent upon completion

### 8.3 Automatic Deletion

Data is automatically deleted when:
- Bot is removed from your server (30-day grace period)
- Inactive servers (no commands for 6 months)
- At your request

## 9. Cookies and Tracking

### 9.1 No Cookies

The Bot does not use cookies or browser-based tracking.

### 9.2 Discord Tracking

Discord may track Bot usage through their platform. Refer to Discord's Privacy Policy for details.

## 10. International Data Transfers

### 10.1 Data Location

Your data may be stored and processed in the United States of America.

### 10.2 International Users

By using the Bot, you consent to data transfer to our storage location, regardless of your country of residence.

## 11. California Privacy Rights (CCPA)

California residents have additional rights:

### 11.1 Right to Know

Request information about data collection and use.

### 11.2 Right to Delete

Request deletion of personal information.

### 11.3 Right to Opt-Out

We don't sell data, so opt-out is not applicable.

### 11.4 Non-Discrimination

We will not discriminate against users who exercise their rights.

**Contact for CCPA Requests:** thereapersarmygaming@gmail.com

## 12. European Privacy Rights (GDPR)

If you're in the EU/EEA, you have rights under GDPR:

### 12.1 Legal Basis

We process data based on:
- Consent (you use the Bot voluntarily)
- Legitimate interests (providing service)
- Contract performance (Terms of Service)

### 12.2 GDPR Rights

- Right of access
- Right to rectification
- Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")
- Right to restrict processing
- Right to data portability
- Right to object
- Rights related to automated decision-making

### 12.3 Data Protection Officer

For GDPR inquiries: Kristopher W. Lee

### 12.4 Supervisory Authority

You have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.

## 13. Changes to This Policy

### 13.1 Updates

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes take effect immediately upon posting.

### 13.2 Notification

Major changes will be announced via:
- Bot status updates
- Support server announcements
- Updated documentation

### 13.3 Continued Use

Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

